<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-344-403  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 344 403.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Business  Jan 23 1989 v15 n2 p62(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Design-for-test tools to the rescue.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Greene, Tony.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The increasing emphasis on application-specific integratedcircuits (ASICs) and semicustom integrated circuits is forcingchip designers to place more importance on testing.andO;Design-to-test tools from companies such as Cadence Inc and TestSystems Strategies Inc (TSSI) are proliferating to fill thedemand.andP;  Cadence Inc provides a high-level programming languagewith its design tools specifically geared for simulation and testvectors.andP;  TSSI markets a neutral format database that is capableof reproducing simulation waveforms and translating them to workwith up to 50 automatic test equipment (ATE) machines.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Semiconductor PreparationTestingApplication-specific integrated circuitsComputer-aided engineering.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>